I"4<p>OpenOakland bridges technology and community for a thriving and equitable Oakland. We do this by:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Cultivating meaningful relationships.</strong><br />
  By partnering with the city and the community we foster a more inclusive, equitable, and engaged Oakland.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Inspiring civic engagement.</strong><br />
  We co-create tools and events that educate Oaklanders on how the city works and inspires them to effect civic change.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Empowering Oaklanders.</strong><br />
  We recognize that Oakland has a rich history of activism. We seek to empower all Oaklanders to keep advocating for our community‘s collective well-being.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>We’re a fiscally-sponsored project of <a href="https://www.codeforamerica.org/">Code for America</a>, a 501(c)3 nonprofit. Donations to OpenOakland are tax-deductible and can be <a href="https://www.codeforamerica.org/donate-to-a-brigade?utm_campaign=Open%20Oakland&amp;utm_source=OpenOakland%20site">made through Code for America</a> (be sure to select OpenOakland from the drop-down menu after choosing the amount).</p>

